204
00:12:41,544 --> 00:12:43,535
Now when I want to see my grandson

205
00:12:43,612 --> 00:12:46,376
I am going to have to make
an appointment with Judith,

206
00:12:46,449 --> 00:12:48,883
who, let's face it,
was never very warm to me.

207
00:12:49,218 --> 00:12:52,381
And what if there's another man there?
Shacking up with her?

208
00:12:52,855 --> 00:12:54,846
Have we even stopped to consider that?

209
00:12:59,395 --> 00:13:01,625
I think he's considering it now, Mom.

210
00:13:02,798 --> 00:13:05,790
- Here's your iced tea, Grandma.
- Thank you, my little angel.

211
00:13:05,868 --> 00:13:07,836
Darling, I asked for a lemon wedge.

212
00:13:11,574 --> 00:13:13,633
All right. Here's what you're going to do.

213
00:13:13,709 --> 00:13:15,836
You and Jake will come live with me.

214
00:13:16,145 --> 00:13:19,808
After all, I'm just rattling around
in that big house all by myself.

215
00:13:20,216 --> 00:13:23,777
That's very considerate, but as soon as
Judith and I work things out,

216
00:13:23,853 --> 00:13:25,514
I'm going to be back at my own house.

217
00:13:25,588 --> 00:13:27,579
Sweetheart, grow up.

218
00:13:29,859 --> 00:13:31,349
Think about what I said.

219
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:35,356
You're my son, and I'll always have room
for you in my house

220
00:13:35,731 --> 00:13:37,164
and in my heart.

221
00:13:38,234 --> 00:13:39,531
I love you, too, Mom.

222
00:13:50,613 --> 00:13:54,071
- I love you, too, Mom.
- Too little. Too late.

223
00:13:57,253 --> 00:14:00,051
- So, Vegas was good?
- It was fine.

224
00:14:00,189 --> 00:14:03,352
Alan, I really want to apologize
for putting you through this.

225
00:14:03,425 --> 00:14:05,620
